	   <tr><td colspan=2>Torsk,<br><br>I'd be glad to run the numbers for you. I don't know your Strength and Weapon skill so I ran them for my stats to get an even comparison. Here they are:<br><br>Ornate Rune Blade:<br><br>Without FBSS: 662<br>With FBSS: 801<br><br>Arbitor's Combine Greatsword<br><br>Without FBSS: 669<br>With FBSS: 810<br><br>Wow, they are both VERY close on damage.&nbsp;&nbsp;Hard to pick one over the other as they are virtually identical.  While the Arbitor's Combine Greatsword wins out just BARELY on the numbers, I doubt you could ever tell the difference when it comes to actual melee damage.<br><br>Like I said, I have used an Arbitor's before on several occasions, and I must say I like it. It does have BIG hits and I can certainly see why people want it and like it. I would like to have one myself and am trying to acquire one ASAP.<br><br>I have never used an Ornate Rune Blade but it sounds like it would be a lot of FUN to use because you are attacking so fast...especially if combined with a haste item or a haste spell from a Chanter or Shammy.<br><br>Basically, it's a toss-up on damage. The Arbitors will probably "appear" to be more impressive because it will roll out those BIG hits from time to time. And if you double for over 100...it's just very cool!  But if you miss, you might as well go get a coke before you swing again! (I'm exaggerating of course, but you get the idea).  <br><br>The Ornate Rune Sword, will nickle and dime the mob to death and do it very quickly, and if you miss, no biggie, you will swing again in a blink of an eye. You won't get the BIG hits that impress your friends, but all in all, it should dish out about the same amount of damage.<br><br>So that brings us to additional Weapon stats. The Arbitor's provides the +15 Wisdom! Now that's hard to beat. So all in all, I'd have to go with the Arbitor's Combine Greatsword if you can combine it with a haste item. There are very few combinations out there that beat it for both damage AND stat bonuses.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>50th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
